This video makes no sense, I am pretty sure the following is cannon, but it could be legends. It's way better story then in the video anyways.

We know about palpatines upbringing and family. His family was rich and had great political power. When he was young Darth Plagesus took him as a apprentice he then killed his family, this made him inherit all the political power. This made him the most qualified candidate for chancellor.

Fast forward through episode 1-6 we see him die at the end of episode 6.

So what do we see in rise of skywalker? Well we know from previous sith lords. After a sith dies they can possess object. It easy to see Palatine use this to possess a clone body of himself. And since Palatine seems to be the strongest sith this possessed body is extremely powerful.
